Slides
=======
* Clustering slide
    - Keep the graph the same size! Don't change the posiiton of the graph
    - Illustrate images being different
        - Have images from different clusters expand, and compare them
        - Make sure this pop up doesn't move other elements around
    - Illustrate images being similar
        - Have additional images pop up from one cluster, and compare to other images from that cluster
        - Make sure this pop up doesn't move other elements around
* Additional noise slide (before existing noise slide)
    - Add a definition of noise
    - Why it is called noise
        - Compare to the term "background noise"
        - Something that is random, hard to interpret
    - Show examples of noise
        - Show image noise
        - Show audio noise
* Additional diffusion model slide (after existing one)
    - Show that different random noise initializations lead to different random outputs
    - Discuss this being a limitation of diffusion models
        - why you see different random outputs when asking for the same prompt
    - Discuss this being useful to identify generated outputs
        - videos sometimes have "random" variation for a single object
            - identities change, objects change
* Additional what is generative AI slide
    - Before the text->text slide
    - Visually appealing illustration of AI model mapping text to different outputs
        - Use chat visualization that's in later slides

